{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":33896,"record_hash":"sha256:d595f94512195e88a0e8a8dde1b787fc08782b4afc3ce133fde0df7b036875f5","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:31:06.854Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Delete File: agent-session-capture/agentlog-sync-lifecycle.md\n*** Add File: agent-session-capture/agentlog-sync-lifecycle.md\n+# Agentlog Sync Lifecycle\n+\n+This note describes the hidden sync command:\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog sync\n+```\n+\n+Capture remains a local operation. Sync is the explicit lifecycle step that uses\n+GitMeta's existing remote exchange semantics to send and receive shareable\n+metadata.\n+\n+## Direction\n+\n+For the POC, do not build agentlog-only GitMeta transport. Agentlog data is\n+stored as normal shareable GitMeta metadata, so the sync command can lean on the\n+existing GitMeta lifecycle:\n+\n+```text\n+pull configured GitMeta metadata\n+push local GitMeta metadata\n+on non-fast-forward, let GitMeta fetch/materialize/serialize and retry\n+```\n+\n+This means `but agentlog sync` may exchange other shareable GitMeta keys in the\n+same configured metadata remote. That is acceptable for the POC and avoids\n+adding scoped refs, scoped materialization state, or custom remote selection\n+before there is enough product pressure for it.\n+\n+## Goals\n+\n+- Reuse GitMeta's existing serialize, pull, push, materialize, and conflict\n+  handling.\n+- Keep `but-agentlog` free of custom Git fetch/push code.\n+- Require an existing GitMeta metadata remote, configured through GitMeta's\n+  normal remote setup.\n+- Keep hook and capture commands local-only and fast.\n+\n+## Non-Goals\n+\n+- Do not sync only `gitbutler:agent-session:*` keys in this POC.\n+- Do not add `--remote`; GitMeta chooses its configured metadata remote.\n+- Do not infer, add, or rewrite Git remotes from `origin`.\n+- Do not implement custom Git transport in `but-agentlog`.\n+- Do not add conflict UI, partial push/pull modes, or background sync policy.\n+\n+## Command Shape\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog sync\n+```\n+\n+The command does not need an agent argument. It operates on stored GitMeta data,\n+not on a live provider transcript.\n+\n+Human output can stay terse:\n+\n+```text\n+Synced GitMeta metadata\n+```\n+\n+JSON output can mirror that with a simple object. More detailed counters are\n+useful later, but not required for the first lifecycle POC.\n+\n+## GitMeta Remote Semantics\n+\n+The command expects GitMeta to have a metadata remote configured. In GitMeta\n+terms, that is a Git remote with `remote.<name>.meta = true`. Setup remains a\n+separate operation, for example through `git meta remote add`.\n+\n+This intentionally avoids a GitButler-specific rule like \"default to `origin`\"\n+or \"create a metadata remote if one is missing.\" Those may become product\n+decisions later, but the POC stays close to GitMeta's existing behavior.\n+\n+## Retry Semantics\n+\n+Keep retries boring and bounded:\n+\n+```text\n+pull metadata from the configured GitMeta remote\n+push local metadata\n+\n+if push is rejected as non-fast-forward:\n+  ask GitMeta to resolve the push conflict\n+  retry push\n+```\n+\n+Stop after a small fixed retry count and fail clearly.\n+\n+## Ordering And Dedupe\n+\n+Remote materialization can merge metadata from multiple machines. Readers should\n+not depend on stored GitMeta list order. After sync, consumers should:\n+\n+- dedupe transcript records by `record_hash`\n+- sort by `source_key` and `record_index` within one source\n+- use `timestamp`, `source_key`, `record_index`, and `record_hash` as stable\n+  ordering inputs across multiple sources\n+\n+This matches the data model documented in\n+[GitMeta Data Model](gitmeta-data-model.md).\n+\n+## Privacy Posture\n+\n+`agentlog sync` should be explicit in the first implementation. Captured\n+transcripts are redacted, but they can still reveal sensitive project context,\n+prompting strategy, file names inside tool commands, and architectural details.\n+\n+Avoid implying that redaction makes transcript data risk-free. Future GitButler\n+UX can decide whether this same primitive runs manually, during branch/PR\n+publish, or as best-effort background sync for opted-in projects.\n+\n+## Decided POC Choices\n+\n+- `but agentlog sync` is a bidirectional metadata sync command.\n+- It uses GitMeta's existing configured metadata remote behavior.\n+- It does not add GitMeta APIs for scoped agentlog refs.\n+- It does not add a remote flag or default to `origin`.\n+- It does not call custom backend ingestion or product-specific sharing logic.\n+- Simplicity is preferred over early isolation; revisit scoped sync only when a\n+  concrete privacy, performance, or product requirement appears.\n+\n+Use [Agentlog Maintainability Playbook](maintainability-playbook.md) at useful\n+checkpoints, especially if sync grows beyond this small wrapper around GitMeta.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:31:06.854Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}